  "prompt": "I have a crush on a girl and do not have courage to propose to her. What should I do to tell her that I like her?",
  "response": "Here are some suggestions to help you express your feelings:\n\n1. Build a friendship first\n- Get to know her better\n- Spend time together\n- Be genuinely interested in her life\n\n2. Start with casual conversations\n- Talk frequently\n- Show your genuine personality\n- Be confident and relaxed\n\n3. Subtle hints and flirting\n- Show interest through body language\n- Give genuine compliments\n- Make her laugh\n- Maintain eye contact\n\n4. Timing and approach\n- Choose a comfortable, private setting\n- Be honest and direct\n- Express your feelings clearly\n- Be prepared for any response\n\n5. Practical steps\n- Ask her out for coffee or a casual activity\n- Share your feelings calmly\n- Don't put too much pressure on her\n- Respect her decision\n\n6. Mental preparation\n- Build self-confidence\n- Be ready for potential rejection\n- Remember that courage matters more than the outcome\n\n7. Communication tips\n- Be sincere\n- Use \"I\" statements\n- Keep it simple and straightforward\n\n8. If she's not interested\n- Accept her response gracefully\n- Maintain respect\n- Preserve the friendship if possible\n\nRemember, confidence and authenticity are key. Good luck!",
